{"/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/1958050101/0407.xml":{"full_text":"Potomac...\n(Continued from Preceding Page)\nrecession into a big depression.\n\nThe crisis that we are suffering\nis essentially a crisis of confi\ndence, not simply one of profits.\nThe big bankers who control\ncredit won\u2019t release it until they\nknow what their cut (interest) is\nto be and what plans, if any, the\ngovernment has for stimulating\nnew production.\nThus far we have had two anti\nrecession measures: a big housing,\nbill and a $1V&-billion increase for\ndefense spending. The latter, of\ncourse, is sheer waste. For unex\nplained reasons the Administra\ntion would rather build arms and\nlet them rust than help small un\nderdeveloped countries get on\ntheir feet.\nReports coming to the office of\nVice President Nixon are that the\npublic is growing a little tired of\nall this indecision by federal of\nficials. A \u201clittle recession\u201d may\nbe good for some people; it\u2019s ob\nviously quite good for the big\ncommercial banks. They have\nmade a killing on the juggling\ncf interest rates.\nBut it\u2019s no good for ordinary\n1 _1 nn nnn^ fAP Rp\nptupic CI1AVA o\npublican politicians. Even Demo\ncrats run a risk when things stay\nbad too long. People get restive\nend begin to talk of thiowing\nthe rascals out\" without regard\nto party label.\n\nRECESSION NOTE\u2014A broken\ndown old car pulled up to the\ntoll gate at the Lincoln Tunnel,\nreports former Congressman T.\nJames Tumulty.\n\u201cFifty cents,\u201d said the collector.\n\u201cSold,\u201d replied the driver.\nFLAG FOR BABY\nFort Campbell, Ky. A tiny\nblue sweater was recently seen\ncn the flag pole under a one-star\ngeneral\u2019s flag at this Army base.\nThe emblems signaled the birth\ncf a fifth son to Brig. Gen. Reu\nben H. Tucker, assistant com\nmander of the 101st Airborne\nDivision.\nDU PONT AND G. M.\nThe Federal Government act\ning under a Supreme Court rul\ning, has submitted a plan for the\nrelease by E. I. du Pont de Ne\nmours Co. of its 63,000,000\nshares of General Motors Corpor\nation. The plan calls for turning\nthe shares over to trustees, who\nwould then be empowered to dis\ntribute the stock to du Pont stock\nholders. __\nJlte Petal Pape)\nEntered at second class matter April\n1W4, at the Poet Mat, Mto\ni ietrpi under Act of March 1 1WI.\nReentered at Pascagoula, Mlsa.\nTELEPHONE DIAL 4-MU\nP. D. EAST Editor\nSUBSCRIPTIONS\nPER YEAR M\nI. ED TURNER\nRealtor\nINSURANCE\nSALES\nRENTALS\nFor Satisfactory and Fast\nResults List Your Property\nWith\nHi\n>*m\n\n\u2019I\n\nk\na p\npn w. nm. enrareaw\nEaslside...\non the way out, for I do not believe in nor practice this form.\nOne type of integration seems to me is not practiced nearly\nenough in Mississippi. This is \u201ckneeling integration. I will\nwelcome any opportuntiy to kneel in prayer with anyone to\nseek a solution to our current dilemma, even those who upon\nreading this may become colorless.\nAt least you are consistent in your business. I understand no\nNegroes may lie in state in your funeral parlor. This is hard for\nme to understand as some of your attitudes suggest you would\nlike to bury a lot of colored folk.\nSincerly yours. John E. Sutphm\n1501 North State\nJackson, Mississippi\nIn the event this nation has a presdient, (And who\ncould doubt it?) he has left some of us more than be\nwildered and befuddled; he has indeed left us gasping.\nAt a press conference, in discussing the recession the\npresident said in his sincere and ponderous, way that he\nbelieved, indeed, that he was convinced that we were at\nan all-time level.\nAnd I thought Dixiecrat semantics were something!\nAs to a recent discussion in Washington as to who\nwould do what in the event the president should become\nunable to do his job, it is humbly suggested that Tricky\nDick Nixon be allowed to sit in while the president is out\nof town. He\u2019d get a lot of experience.\n\u201cThere are only two classes of men in the United\nStates: those who work for their living and those who\nvote for them.\u201d H. L. Mencken.\nI -\u2019M \u00ab\u00bbAY IT WITH FLOWOir s fVf f\nw. T\u00abi\u00abpirk rwvmi!\nANNETTE STEMME FLORISTS\nMmtbm 1 Th* P.T.D.\nDial 2-1937 Phone Night Sunday 2-1401\n125 W. Front Greenhouse 802 Hall Av\u00ab.\nMato thosa form impfovainetiff wfHi\nfa* rfflffffi\nYoa probably know the money-aaving* predtwnoklng\nadvantages of concrete for farm use. Yai may eateknow\nwhat you aave by using our Ready-Mfared Coiadaf Yai\n\u25a0aye tim% because you do no buyiag, hondHfagbJatariag\nej material t, You save money, becausemd\nhelpers' time is money. You save delays, baoosMO we\ndeliver when forms are ready. You oavO'.weata *4\nlsflovse afasada*\nLet us deliver Ready-Mixed Concrete for. your list fatal\nimprovement job. A little, or a lot, well quote pma\nSoutheastern. Materials Co.\nv .-A,\nAgain In 1958, United Gas advertises to\nvTO THE GULF SOUTH\nV r\ni m\n\n-\u2019,v\ni.\nts\u00bb s \u2022\"1.\nt,\n\n3-ii\nr.\u00bb.\n4\nK&i.;.\n\na\nVi\n.vi\ntin\n*r\nJ i i SH.. M' fL j| r\n\nr","height":"22032","width":"14475"}}
